#: ../../B/Berzerkeley.rst:5
msgid "Berzerkeley"
msgstr "Berzerkeley"

#: ../../B/Berzerkeley.rst:7
msgid "/b\\@r·zer´klee/, n\\."
msgstr "/b\\@r·zer´klee/, 名詞"

#: ../../B/Berzerkeley.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from ‘berserk’, via the name of a now-deceased record label; poss. "
"originated by famed columnist Herb Caen] Humorous distortion of \"Berkeley\""
" used esp. to refer to the practices or products of the :ref:`BSD` Unix "
"hackers. See :ref:`software-bloat`\\, :ref:`Berkeley-Quality-Software`\\."
msgstr ""
"[‘berserk(逆上した)’から、今は亡きレコードレーベルの名前を経由して。おそらく名コラムニストHerb "
"Caenが生み出した]「Berkeley」のユーモラスな変形で、特に\\ :ref:`BSD`\\ Unixハッカーの慣行や産物を指すのに使う。\\ "
":ref:`software-bloat`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Berkeley-Quality-Software`\\ を参照。"

#: ../../B/Berzerkeley.rst:14
msgid ""
"Mainstream use of this term in reference to the cultural and political "
"peculiarities of UC Berkeley as a whole has been reported from as far back "
"as the 1960s."
msgstr "UCバークレー全体の文化的・政治的な風変わりさを指すこの用語の一般的な使用は、1960年代までさかのぼって報告されている。"
